article.description: Terrence Hargrove Jr. had 27 points as Saint Louis beat Maryville (MO) 82-69 on Tuesday night. Javonte Perkins added 22 points for the Billikens.
article.headline: Hargrove leads Saint Louis past Maryville (MO) 82-69
article.linkText: Hargrove leads Saint Louis past Maryville (MO) 82-69
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Terrence Hargrove Jr. had 27 points as Saint Louis beat Maryville (MO) 82-69 on Tuesday night. Javonte Perkins added 22 points for the Billikens. Jordan Goodwin had 18 points, 15 rebounds, six assists and six steals for Saint Louis (9-2), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Yuri Collins added seven assists. Parker Long had 18 points for the Saints. Jalen Gant added 12 points. Dezmond McDaniel had 11 points. Saint Louis takes on Kansas State on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
